			.text-block.odd
				h2 Community
				.text
					p Right now, in San Francisco and the whole the Bay Area, we have the opportunity to strengthen our roots as a diverse community, one that is devoted to the commons and to learning, to accessibility, celebration and intergenerational connection.

					.image-grid
						.img-grid.wide(style="background-image:url(images_arcadium/community_2.jpg)")
						.img-grid.wide(style="background-image:url(images_arcadium/community_3.jpg)")


					blockquote
						.quote-textLorem “The Arcadium will infuse energy, magnetism, and cultural creativity into a jewel of the city. What’s striking to me is the project’s deep engagement with artists, entrepreneurs, culture-bearers, and local and national organizations. This commitment promises to enliven and connect each of the communities it will serve, in an ecosystem curated with impeccable care.”
						.author
							| Nina Simons, Co-Founder of 
							a(href="http://www.bioneers.org", title="Bioneers") Bioneers
							|  & Founder of 
							a(href="http://www.bioneers.org/every-womans-leadership", title="Everywoman’s Leadership") Everywoman’s Leadership

					.image-grid
						.img-grid.tall(style="background-image:url(images_arcadium/community_1.jpg)")
						.img-grid.tall(style="background-image:url(images_arcadium/community_4.jpg)")

				.more.text
					p Community engagement and participation is the bedrock principle of our endeavor. It is neither an obligation, nor a platitude. Instead it is our calling, privilege and joy.
					p We will host participatory events to solicit feedback and guide vendor selection at a scale more often associated with social movements than real estate projects. Ongoing engagement with our communities of visitors and vendors will ensure that the variety and quality of our programming exceed expectations. And during our construction phase, a Direct Public Offering will provide opportunity for financial involvement at a low minimum investment threshold.

				.more-button More

			.text-block
				h2 Culture
				.text
					p The Arcadium San Francisco will will craft unique visitor experiences by spotlighting cultural offerings from San Francisco and the Bay Area. <strong>Performance</strong> and <strong>studio space</strong>, <strong>contemporary galleries</strong>, <strong>arts education and therapy</strong>, and <strong>large-scale installations</strong> will inform, inspire and engage.

					.image-grid
						.img-grid.tall(style="background-image:url(images_arcadium/culture_2.jpg)")
						.img-grid.tall(style="background-image:url(images_arcadium/culture_3.jpg)")



					blockquote
						.quote-textLorem “ArtSpan is enthusiastic to contribute to this vision by providing San Francisco artists a platform to showcase their work on an international stage. By leveraging our 40-year history connecting the entire city of San Francisco to art and artists, we will offer an authentic Bay Area creative experience to city residents and visitors alike with dedicated art creation space, rotating programming and events, and community engagement in neighborhoods throughout San Francisco. The new Palace complex will offer the first ever combination working studio spaces coupled with a polished fine art gallery.” 
						.author Joen Madonna, Executive Director of ArtSpan 

					.image-grid
						.img-grid.wide(style="background-image:url(images_arcadium/culture_1.jpg)")
						.img-grid.wide(style="background-image:url(images_arcadium/culture_4.jpg)")

				.more.text
					p Collaboration with cultural stewards will bring this program to life. With local community arts organizations and national arts foundations, we will offer residencies to Bay Area and international artists, with rotating exhibitions in permanent spaces and throughout the building. Contemporary galleries will set a stage for expanded discussion and commercial activity. The Arcadium is a place for the entire creative process -an immersive interplay between artists at work and people performing, learning, interacting, or buying. 
					p Stage and theatre space, as found at the Palace of Fine Arts, will be programmed with education, film, and performance institutions and community organizations. In public spaces, cultural heritage exhibits will set a discourse for the meeting place of past and future.
				
				.more-button More

			.text-block.odd
				h2 Commerce
				.text
					p We are forming a principled ecosystem of commercial and local service offerings including farm-to-table restaurants, fair trade boutiques, co-working space and other community oriented services designed to welcome, delight, nourish and sustain.

					.image-grid
						.img-grid.wide(style="background-image:url(images_arcadium/commerce_1.jpg)")
						.img-grid.wide(style="background-image:url(images_arcadium/commerce_4.jpg)")



					blockquote
						.quote-textLorem “Kitchener Oakland is a commercial kitchen for startup food entrepreneurs to cook and grow in. We have crafted a community-oriented and affordable space that supports micro and small businesses with big potential. I'm incredibly excited to collaborate with the Arcadium San Francisco to provide a plant-based commissary kitchen paired with an open-layout teaching kitchen. This combination of commerce and education will be hub for people to discover and share delicious food and promote environmental sustainability.”
						.author Sophia Chang, Owner/Founder of Kitchener 
					.image-grid
						.img-grid.tall(style="background-image:url(images_arcadium/commerce_3.jpg)")
						.img-grid.tall(style="background-image:url(images_arcadium/commerce_2.jpg)")
				
				.more.text
					p Eateries are the literal and figurative hearth of the Arcadium SF, offering whole food plant-based cuisine with a commitment to accessibility, health, and environmental sustainability. The open-layout teaching and commissary kitchens make up a central hub, where small food entrepreneurs will provide food to be enjoyed on-site or taken home.
					p Regenerative commerce prioritizes environmental sustainability and human wellbeing as a functional foundation for commercial enterprise. The vendor ecosystem of the Arcadium SF will form around the overarching goals regenerating commerce, restoring community, renewing culture and embodying care. Our selection criteria can be found on page 27 of our Palace of Fine Arts Conceptual proposal.

				.more-button More

			.text-block
				h2 Care
				.text
					p In an interconnected world, caring for fellow humans, our environment, and our cultural history is integral to caring for our future. More than a virtue, we strive for embodied care through our work, our relationships and our principles. We believe Care is the strongest thread that links neighborhoods and human beings in the Bay Area. At the Arcadium SF, we will tend to the body and the spirit with holistic wellness services and a new club that strengthens, builds and expands the acumen, power and positive impact of women. 



					.image-grid
						.img-grid.tall(style="background-image:url(images_arcadium/care_1.jpg)")
						.img-grid.tall(style="background-image:url(images_arcadium/care_2.jpg)")

					blockquote
						.quote-textLorem “This organization is what we all need! An incredible vision for ‘place and space’ to actively support women's growth, development, connections and, most importantly, ability to thrive. It’s inspired and practical—in equal measure. Improving the lives of women means improving the lives of all humans and the planet we share- a planet whose very survival is entrusted to us.”
						.author Kathy LeMay, Founder of Raising Change 

					.image-grid
						.img-grid.wide(style="background-image:url(images_arcadium/care_3.jpg)")
						.img-grid.wide(style="background-image:url(images_arcadium/care_4.jpg)")

				.more.text
					p A wellness pavilion will bring together integrative health clinics, nutritious food offerings, a therapeutic destination spa, and additional spaces for yoga, movement, fitness and dance.
					p As an anchor tenant, Flow Global is a gathering place for women and their guests, and an educational institution focused on financial acumen, self development and social impact with workshops curated by a team of global women leaders in their fields. 
					p Connection promotes health, and facilitating shared participatory experiences over food, art, and social impact is the underlying ethic embodied in this building. We will partner with preeminent organizations that view health and healing from this perspective.

				.more-button More


